thread.title: Stable Dollar Keeps Global Markets From Blowout

author: Mike Bird
title: Stable Dollar Keeps Global Markets From Blowout
text:
While investors have fretted that stocks and credit are overvalued this year, in one market prices may be at their most balanced in years: currencies.
Volatility returned with a bang to global stocks this year, interrupting a bull market that began almost a decade ago and raising investor concerns about the durability of a yearslong rally.
